\subsection{3. Missing values in output}{

The last \code{a} rows of \code{poisson} and \code{inc} are \code{NA}, where
\code{a = min(which(delay_dist > 0)) - 1} is the minimum number of days from
infection to reporting. For \code{a > 0}, the probability that an infection
between day \code{length(x)-a} and day \code{length(x)-1} is reported between day
\code{0} and day \code{length(x)-1} is zero, so the supplied reported incidence
time series provides no information about incidence on those \code{a} days.
